Summary: For the money, the Seirus Innovation Balaclava is an excellent choice, especially if you want to be comfortable and warm ...
Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Men', 'Accessories', 'Hats & Caps', 'Balaclavas']]
Review Text: Probably the best thing about the Seirus Innovation Balaclava is that it can be worn three different ways, depending on what you want to use it for.  You can wear is as a masque, hood, or clava.  If you simply want to keep the back of your neck  and head warm you'd set it up as a hood, whereas if the temperatures dip low you can wear it as a full-faced clava, with only your eyes showing.  If you run, walk, ski, or are in the outdoors for any extended period of time, a balaclava is a more than welcome piece of apparel.  No futzing with a scarf to keep your mouth and nose warm and you can easily put a hat over the top.The Seirus is quite reasonably priced and the fleece is of a nice, soft quality.  Make sure before you order that your get the proper sizing.  They come in three sizes that range from XS for young children to L/XL for adults.  If you are worried about any sort of smell, it's best to wash the balaclava prior to wearing it.  The fabric is Polartec and in order to preserve the Durable Water Repellant (DWR), the last thing you need to do is throw this in the washing machine using your normal detergent.  Probably the best thing to do is if you want to wash it, do so by hand using a little bit of blue Dawn dish detergent.  For the money, the Seirus Innovation Balaclava is an excellent choice, especially if you want to be comfortable and warm.

Summary: Fun, cute, comfy, but advise buying in person
Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'V', 'Vibram'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Shoes', 'Athletic', 'Running']]
Review Text: Actually they are adorable. I tried some - both barefoot and with toesocks - at a local store that thinks everything they have is made of gold, then reluctantly ordered them online, having not seen this gray/bright yellow/green version that I bought, in person. As soon as they got on my feet, I realized I was delighted with their zany but relatively subdued looks.I had gone into that store looking to replace my current running shoes (which I did) but when I saw these things I knew I had to have some, especially when I discovered that they made my feet so happy.I don't recommend buying these online if there is any way you can get around it. For one thing, each flavor of these Vibram FiveFingers professes a different fit. I found an excellent chart for that on the Campmor website. But in addition, you need to know that each pair can vary. With a shoe that has this kind of fit (as with any shoe, really), it doesn't take much variation in material or stitching or lamination process to produce a "hot spot". In my case I'm dealing with bunions that are static at this time but which must be babied in order to keep them static. That's the reason I buy the LS or laced version which is easier to adjust. I tie a square knot in the laces above the first or second lace hole on most lace shoes, to keep that area from tightening too much when I pull them tight enough to make the arch and ankle areas happy.At any rate, this pair fit differently than the ones in the full-price store. Luckily I was able to make needed adjustments because return is a bummer. Again, I advise buying only what you can try on, especially for this shoe.I personally am not going to run in these. I ran for years but realized my brother was right when he declared that "anyone over 50 who runs is asking for hip replacement". That's even true for people who don't carry extra weight. Nope, not gonna run but oh how I love that barefoot feeling all day around the house and yard. I might wear these on my daily hike but like them too much to subject them to the inevitable wear on pavement. Plus they're just too cute for words and appeal to my sense of quirkiness.Comment Comment | Permalink

Review Text: I loved my Keen sandals, mostly due to nice fit, they were a little sweatty though.  So much that I bought the shoes (very good), bought the work boots (steel toed also very good), bought the socks (not so good).I don't honestly wear the H2 sandals that much, maybe had them about a year (bought them last late summer/fall), but live in the northeast so its mostly a summer shoe, 4 -5 months a year or so.  So we went to Grand Tetons, these were my "off hiking day" shoes for the trip.  We did a 6 mile flat hike and the backs ripped out of one of them. By the way the socks have holes in the sides (not heals or toes like you might expect).  Used to be all their products seemed to have 5 star ratings... me thinks the expansion to all kinds of shoes may be causing some kind of performance issues.So not much use, the treads on the bottom frankly look brand new but the heels ripped.  I dunno if I will get another Keen shoe, I am seeing some of their newer stuff has some bad ratings.  Still I'd take them over almost anything Teva, but not at full price. I guess I would take another shot for $50 or $60... but for $100 they need to last more than a season.

My teenage daughter thinks the watch is super cute and wanted to wear it immediately.  I think it is cute, but will only wear it for casual events.3 stars because of the plastic.Edit: This watch comes in a variety of colors, and, in my opinion, the wilder colors are more fitting to this watch style.

Review Text: I bought my first pair of Havianas about eight years ago when we were vacationing in Mexico.  I had never heard of them, but needed a new pair of flip flops when the ones I had with me broke a strap.  That first pair finally gave out last summer (one of the straps pulled out from the bottom of the shoe), so I just ordered the bronze and white/rose ones.I'm a 7.5, and the 37/38 fits perfectly. I also really like the slim design of these; if you have wider feet, though, definitely order a regular pair.Yes, they do seem pricey for a pair of flip flops, but the cushioned foot bed is incredibly comfortable and they last forever.  Amazon also carries them at discounted prices, if you're willing to poke around a bit here.I look forward to many years of good use from my new Havianas!

Summary: Adult Hanes Tagless Long Sleeve T-shirt
Categories: [['Sports & Outdoors', 'Clothing', 'Men', 'Shirts', 'T-Shirts'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Men', 'Clothing', 'Shirts', 'T-Shirts'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Men', 'Big & Tall']]
Review Text: I bought this t-shirt in 5 different colors- white, black, royal blue, ash, & light steel. I wear them for pj tops, primarily, but also for layering.  I was expecting "ComfortSoft"(Hanes trademark), but that's not what I got. I only wear Hanes underwear, and mostly, their short sleeve t-shirts.  I buy them under the "ComfortSoft" label, as they're very comfortable, wash well, and are very durable.  These "Tagless" shirts are not!  They're made of a heavier weight cotton, and they're somewhat scratchy, right out of the dryer. They did fit well, right out of the bag, but started shrinking, the first time I washed them. The white one, in particular, has shrunk in the arms to where they go half-way up my forearms. The others haven't shrunk as much, but are very snug right now, and I can't imagine how much longer I'll be able to wear them. I've only had them about 6 weeks. Incidentally, I came back to Amazon today, and searched for "ComfortSoft" long sleeve tees.  I found some, from a different supplier, but there was a note at the top of the screen that I had ordered these previously.  When I put some in my cart, and went to check out, they had surprisingly changed from "ComfortSoft", to "Tagless", so I deleted them.  I guess I'll have to find them somewhere else.  I am VERY disappointed in Hanes right now.

Review Text: i am so happy these came back!usually because i am not 'seeing' what i am buying i only go for the minimum amount until i know for sure i am impressed with the quality. unfortunately by the time these got to me in Guyana, South America and i realized they were fantastic-they were also out of stock!! but i kept checking almost every week hoping they would return-AND THEY DID!! I find this sports bra to be the most flattering and sturdy one I've ever tried on.  I'm a small C-cup, so I can't really speak for women who have larger chests.. but I found the support sufficient enough for my "girls".I found the bra to be true to size.. I'm a 32-34C at VS and I purchased the 34C.  Very pleased.  I will, however, add that I feel the material could be a bit thicker in the cups region as it will definitely show if you are cold..!Great bra with adjustable shoulder straps and 3-sets of hook closures to adjust for chest width.  No uni-boob.  Wonderful bra!

Review Text: I feel like, "what can one say when one word can pretty much sum it up? How about "Perfect".I get comments on this all the time -- it's very classy, wears well, keeps time great, and is, well, just awesome.  It looks and feels like it costs 10x what I paid.The only thing about this watch is that it's challenging to adjust or set an alarm.  I don't use any of those features, to be fair, so perhaps I'd get more used to it if I used it for that.  Cell phones and other gadgets have replaced those needs for me, but when I wanted to use it, I certainly had to get out the manual and read it carefully.  Not worth it.  But for me, it's worth it just to have it as a classy, solidly build timepiece that draws just enough attention to it that it stays classy.  I never get tired of looking at its pearl-white-like bezel coloring, the deep, rich blacks in the face (and the band).  And the clasp is well built.Love this watch.

Categories: [['Sports & Outdoors', 'Accessories', 'Sport Watches'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'New Arrivals'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Jewelry: International Shipping Available'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Available for International Shipping'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Sport Watches'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Timex'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Timex test'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Watches', 'Wrist Watches'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', "Women's Athletic Watches"]]
Review Text: I love this watch.Here's a few things you need to know about me:1. I'm a weebit OCPD and I obsess over time. Wearing a digital watch synced up with my computer time exactly is a comfort to me. I've worn a watch since I was 7 and my husband can attest he has never seen me without my trusty digital wrist watch.2. I abuse my watches. I sleep, eat, drink, shower, run, swim, go to the beach, etc with my watches. All my watches end up with scratched surfaces. An unlucky few had their faces broken into. A lot of my watchbands couldn't stand the abuse and committed suicide.3. I lose/break watches like it's my job. By the time I was 22, I have gone through 13 watches. The fastest record of me losing or breaking a watch was 1 hour. No watch has ever lived more than 2 years on my wrist...until now.Now, here's the review:My coworker told me Ironman watches are indestructible, so I had to give it a try. When my watch inevitably died, I gave T5D601 a try. Well, that was a good watch, but the watch band design was flawed. Where the watch band connects to the watch was glued on, and it eventually failed. The watch lasted a year. When my watches die, I normally go into panic mode and head straight to a store where I think they might sell watches to buy a replacement watch. This time, I dragged my poor husband (then boyfriend) who was on a date with me at the time to a store to buy my trusty Ironman watch against his will. I NEEDED it! Life was not complete without my watch! I wasn't going to buy another watch where the watch band was glued on, so after some debating I ended up with this model. It looked sturdy and indestructible. It looked like it might last. I was right.That was four years ago. This is the only watch I've ever had that lasted over two years. It's still alive. Two years ago the pink face plate fell off. I superglued it back on and it has never been a problem since. The pink color is painted on, and a lot of it peeled off over time. Fortunately the plastic underneath has also been dyed a pink color, so it's not obvious that the paint peeled off. The face has six scratches, two of them deep, but the watch is still functional. The band shows no sign of deterioration except for the horrendous scratch marks I caused, which is remarkable.Function:In terms of function, it has three alarms, the normal stuff, I wish it has a count down, but it doesn't. Any function you don't need you can hide. I run, but since I have a Garmin 305, I never used the lap function on this watch. It allows you to set two time zones, and all you have to do is to long press the start button to change time zone permanently. If you want to just see what the other place's time is, just press start button and not hold it down. This function comes in handy for me. I actually use it for daylight savings time.This watch has been to hell and back with me and it is still alive. Four years is an amazing record for me. IMO, it's not the prettiest looking watch out there. My husband tried to buy me a Citizen Eco-Drive to get me away from this hideous watch (his opinion) but I would have none of it. It may not be dressy or beautiful, but it is dependable and it does not fail, which, for me, is more important than anything else.

Review Text: I bought this a few weeks ago and absolutely love them.  I am a size 8 1/2 in a sneaker so I ordered the size 8 figuring I didn't want them to slip off while in the deep end of the pool.  They fit great.  They are a bit snug on the top of the foot by the zipper but they don't start to bother me until about 2 hours into my exercize program.  Yes, I am in the water doing aerobics that long.  I walk in the shallow (4 foot) section for about a half hour and then go into the 17 foot deep section for about an hour to an hour and a half for aquajogging and calisthenics.  Only if I keep pressing one foot on top of the other does the zipper bother me.  I learned to keep my feet flush against the sides of one another and problem solved.  No worries of catching any nasty bugs from other people's feet and I am now enjoying my workouts alot more than before when all I thought about was catching athlete's foot or plantar's warts (not to mention the other things I don't even know about).  I am now ordering another 2 pairs just to have backups.

Categories: [['Sports & Outdoors', 'Accessories', 'Sport Watches'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'New Arrivals'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Sport Watches'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Men', 'Watches', 'Wrist Watches'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', "Men's Athletic Watches"]]
Review Text: This is my second G-Shock watch, and it was exactly what I expected. It is a high end sport watch. I bought this because I kill nice watches (at least the ones that can be had for $100 or less), but the G-Shocks appear to stand the abuse of spending 8 hours a day on my wrist at work with no complaints. Except for a brief period after daylight savings time starts, its always accurate due to the atomic clock signal. Even the bands are specially made to be tougher than normal (which is why I've never broken one, a rarity for me if not a miracle), the huge (and kind of ugly) rubber-over-metal bumper keeps the face from getting scratched which is good for me as well. This is also a solar powered watch, and my last one is still going strong after more than 4 years, so I can safely say battery life is excellent. The analog display is easy to read day and night, but the extra light is an old pre-indiglo type. I don't really use all the extra bells and whistles, and it's still a little drab looking. On the whole though, its nicer than many sport watches, and won't break.

Review Text: I loved traveling with this Pacsafe handbag. It was roomy to carry several different items at different times: bottles of water, rain ponchos, my quart-size bag of liquids for going through airport security, tech peripherals, etc. Plenty of organization - it has a nice outer pocket for travel maps, journal, memo pads or other documents (note: this exterior pocket just has a zipper and does not have the additional zipper clip security), an outer pocket on each end (one is somewhat tight - used it for glasses; the other is a bit more expandable and used it for bulkier sunglasses or a small water bottle). Additional organization includes a zippered pocket inside (where I stored my wallet and passport), 3 interior pockets on one side of the bag (for cell phone, pens, etc. and includes one with RFID protection), and a large interior compartment pocket on the other side.  AND the interior of the bag is a light cream color - not black - so you can see everything very easily. The only reason for the 4 stars is that the strap was sometimes uncomfortable on my shoulder when I had weightier things in the bag (I am thinking of purchasing a seat belt pad for the next time I use it - possibly the "Bell 22-1-33240-8 Black Memory Foam Seat Belt Pad"), and I couldn't keep the strap buckle in place; over time it would slide out of adjustment.  However, there may be instructions for securing the strap buckle which I did not read.

Review Text: These are good all-around hiking boots. They really do keep your feet warm and dry. My daughter and I (who wears the same size) share these. She actually used them snow-shoeing and said they were fine. The construction seems good. No problems at all. I do think the traction could use some improvement. It's not bad but I have a super good-quality pair of boots that I'm comparing them to. I just don't see why some of these hiking boots on the market have such crappy traction. Traction is one of the most important qualities of a good boot. I probably won't buy this brand again because it wasn't until I received them that I realized they are made in China, just like Merrell and all the other well-known brands. I'm not buying from these companies anymore.

Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Clothing', 'Lingerie, Sleep & Lounge', 'Intimates', 'Shapewear', 'Waist Cinchers']]
Review Text: I have several corsets and waist cinchers and I have to say that this one is my favourite. I have worn it almost daily since I bought it, and I couldn't be more pleased. Allow me to explain why this is the cincher to buy.1)The difference between corsets and cinchers: I own both, and they both do different things even though most people think that they're the same. A corset makes the body look beautiful outside of clothes (they push the breasts up very high and pull in the waist), but in general (unless you're wearing Marie Antoinette style clothing) they don't look good under an outfit. The breasts become a single lump and the ties are usually quite visiable underneath (which defeats the entire purpose of trying to get people to think that this is your natural figure). A cincher is made to be worn under clothes, to pull in the waist, and to be as invisiable as possible. Therefore they often aren't as pretty as corsets but make much better undergarments.2) Rago rocks! I own many shaper garments, and Rago's are by far the best. Yes, you can find cheaper brands in the department stores, but they won't hold up as well and they won't have the power that Rago's have.3)Of the versions Rago offers on this site, this one is the best. I own the other model which is very similar except that it is lace and has garters, but it doesn't offer as much support as this one and aren't as invisiable as this one. The satin feels wonderful next to the skin and even under clingy dresses this is just about undetectable. Unless you have your heart set on garters, this is the cincher to buy.4) The fit: like many women I suffer from "Mummy Tummy", the horrible price one must pay for having grown two human beings in her body. I am in very good shape, but nothing gets those muscles back to their prepregnancy shape besides surgery (I don't have a spare $20,000 lying around and the scar is huge and ugly). This garment instantly takes 2-4 inches off of the waist and allows one to wear fashionable clothes again without looking frumpy or silly. Another bonus is that I stood about two inches taller because it forces you to walk and sit with perfect posture. This gave me back my youthful waistline. One reviewer said that the fit is a bit tight and they run small; the fit is much tighter than what lace materials and cheaper brands offer but that's because it's a high quality product that works! Those satin panels really pull you in, but they're not uncomfortable (I felt like a sausage for the first hour I wore it, but the body heat warms it up and makes it softer without losing any control). I plan on losing about 10-20 lbs. over the next few months so I will probably buy a new one soon, but I'd recommend buying your size according to the chart. Most of the time I can fit into a small because they don't provide as much compression, but this one you need to be exact.Anyway, if you are looking for an awesome waist cincher that is affordable, flattens your stomach and gives you a lovely "wasp's waist", and feels wonderful and comfortable next to the skin, this is the one to buy.

Summary: Scratchy material; fabric pills easily; not as durable as my Glamorise bras
Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Clothing', 'Lingerie, Sleep & Lounge', 'Intimates', 'Bras', 'Everyday Bras'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Plus-Size', 'Intimates', 'Bras', 'Everyday Bras']]
Review Text: This bra is highly rated on Amazon, which made me want to give it a shot. My mother warned me, "Don't buy Playtex!", because she felt they came up too high under the arms with excess fabric and that their cups fit weirdly compared to other brands in the same size. But I bought this anyway, mostly because it was half the cost of my fave brand, Glamorise. Boy, did I make a mistake!Okay, I will say that this covers and holds the bo*bs up just fine. Almost too well- it reminds me of that "Lunch Lady Song" Adam Sandler sang on SNL years ago, about a lady who has 76 hooks in her big old bra or something like that. That's how I felt while wearing this! Granted, I'm a big woman but my chest isn't sagging that much (yet) and I don't need the "duct tape holding method" that this bra feels like. I wear a 48F and this bra just didn't feel right to me. Not tight or with any spillover...just icky. As my mother warned, there is indeed too much fabric on the sides of the bra under the arm. Maybe women with a lot of fat in that area like this extra fabric, but that's actually one of my lean spots (genetics and years of weight-training to thank), so all it does is rub against my upper arms and underarms (which feels awful, too).The fabric is also SO scratchy! Really uncomfortable on my skin all day long. I always hand-wash my bras/panties alone, rinse well and then let them drip dry. My delicates last for years this way. And I have never had a bra with fabric that felt so rough! This bra pilled along the edges, too, which doesn't happen to any other bra that I have (mostly because I hand-wash and drip-dry, I'm sure). Forget 18 hours- after 6 hours, I couldn't wait to tear this scratchy bra off!The straps are just too thick for me. Unless you're wearing a crewneck, these may peek out of your shirts because there's so much to the straps and cups. The bra comes up high on the chest, too, which is fine if concealing your breasts is your goal. But for those who wear ballet-neck, v-neck or sweetheart necklines, this bra comes up too high on the chest and the straps are too wide.I praise Amazon for carrying many bras for plus-sized women like me. I just don't care for this bra and will purchase Glamorise (despite the extra cost) because I've learned my lesson. I DID try another kind of Playtex bra and didn't like it, either (similar problems).

Summary: great shoes, but they don't last
Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Shoes & Accessories: International Shipping Available'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'S', 'Speedo'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Shoes', 'Athletic', 'Water Shoes']]
Review Text: I have been buying and using these shoes for years and years, and the quality has always been great. I use them for gardening, and then swimming right after (I do both every single day) and they hold up to both. They are great traction and protection in the garden, and they are great for swimming laps and pushing off from flip turns.I usually wear a 6.5 in women's shoes and a 6 in these shoes fits fine.My issue is this: for the last several months, I have been going through these shoes like crazy. With daily use, I'm having to buy a new pair every month- either the sole gets holes in it, or the top of the shoes rips/stretches so it doesn't fit anymore. Nothing has changed about the conditions or usage (same pool, same garden surface, same amount of wear) but apparently the quality of these shoes has gone REALLY downhill. They just aren't as durable. But they are comfy and they protect my feet, so I keep buying them- I haven't found a shoe that fits as great.The other issue, and this has always been a problem- the innersole of the shoe slips. It's firmly in place when the show arrives, but after a few wears it pulls up from the bottom of the shoe and "floats around" as you walk/swim/etc. It's a pain in the neck. But, again, because of the fit of these shoes, I put up with it.However, I'm definitely on the search for a better shoe- if I can find one with similar fit, nice thick grippy sole, and as lightweight, I would switch in a heartbeat.

Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'ASICS'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Men', 'Shoes', 'Athletic', 'Walking']]
Review Text: Subtracting 1 star for these reasons: Firstly, insole is not easily removable without some ripping at bottom(glued) . Secondly, runs a trifle small. I usually wear a 10 4E, in Asics, had to go for 10.5 in this style, and fits well: hugging the heel, and opening up nicely at the ball of the foot with unobtrusive, gentle arch support. I have used the shoe for a few days, as a trainer (treadmill walking, some weights). The shoe appears well made, does every thing moderately well (Fit, style, comfort/cushioning). Nothing  very stellar. I believe it is an excellent value for the money, and is almost equal in performance, albeit with more stability to Asics lower end Neutral runners. I have tried them and concluded that it is better than the Gel strike & Gel contend. Gel equationASICS Men's Equation 6 Running Shoeseems to have more cushioning( if that's your thing), primarily because of a thicker insole. Had it not been for the garish fluorescent green highlights and sole, I would wear it casually. I have also tried the new Gel express 4ASICS Men's Gel-Express 4 Running Shoe....seems mostly identical, and would be a good choice if  express 3 unavailable in your size.

Review Text: Very picky guy -- said he "would NEVER dream of buying shoes online" where he couldn't try them on first. Says these are the most comfortable shoes he's ever worn in his life and will die with these on his feet because he doesn't want to wear anything else on his 9EEE wide feet (I purchased a 10M in Expresso for him)! He has heel spurs and arch challenges -- so the material the soles are made of have been a great source of relief for him. I can't think of a better way to put it than he described when thanking me for buying these for him! He especially appreciates being able to adjust the top for foot swelling -- everyone's feet swell at varying degrees throughout the day -- but I guess older folks find that very uncomfortable to manage. These shoes answered to a lot of comfort issues he had with other foot coverings -- you really can't go wrong here.

Review Text: I purchased this at a local store.  I am 67" and approx 165 lbs.  My waist is approx 33-35 in.  Well, I wanted something to slim my tummy whenever I feel "puffy".  I have tried soo many other products, and this too will end up at the top of my closet.So, here's the thing:  I cannot wear it under a form fitting shirt, all the hooks, rods, etc, show thru. It holds tight to the top and bottom, but that mid (most important) section, bulges right thru.  And to add a reason that makes most shapewear suck, is the fact that I am STUCK with it.  You cannot (and should not) return under garments.  So, for anyone who is undecided, I realize the 5-Star ratings seem promising, but I strongly suggest you try something else.  If nothing else, go to a local store because it would REALLY suck if you pay S&H; to have this disappointment DELIVERED!

Review Text: First off, I have to say that this is a very expensive flip flops. Besides the glitter and the orthapedic structure in the sole there is nothing really special about them. When I first saw these I was thinking I would get more than one pair but one pair is enough and the only reason I am not returning is because I used some of my rewards toward them and don't want the hassel. I do like that these can at least be worn to a water park because the sole is like a durable rubber which water would not harm. I ordered my exact size and I am glad I did because a size down would have definitely been too small. These could have used wider straps to make them more appealing or to help them look like more than just a glitter flip flop. I guess since they are orthapedic my feet will be happy but I definitely would not get another pair of these. I thought I was getting something a little more. Almost 70 bucks for  "flip flops" is just not cool.

Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Clothing', 'Lingerie, Sleep & Lounge', 'Intimates', 'Accessories', 'Pads & Enhancers']]
Review Text: I didn't purchase mine from Amazon but I did buy these online last summer (eBay) and am now looking for another style as these did not work out for me, so I've only worn them once or twice and they are in my GoodWill drop-off bag. I did find them to be very heavy when bending down as another reviewer mentioned--and way too hot to wear in the summer. Beads of perspiration formed  beneath the silicone inserts, dripping down and tickling to distraction as they pooled in my bra cup. They were also visible past the edges of my bra so I had to be very careful not to wear anything that was cut too low thus revealing my secret. They are also too wide for my 34" chest, making me look like I'm flat and fatty in the upper body instead of well endowed. I weigh 110# and am 5'2"--but it doesn't take much to make a short person like me look like I gained 5 lbs with this spread out bust bulk. It is too thick on the lateral edges of the chest instead of being fuller in the middle which is what I was hoping for. I am a cross between a 34 A and B and need something to fill in my bra a bit better, but this really only fills out the sides and is too wide all around,extending past the bra edges and just makes me look like I have a flat fatty chest. I am about to order a wedge silicone style that has a push up effect according to the reviews with the hope that it will be cooler and tolerable for the summer because it has a smaller surface area, and that it will give me a perkier look with fuller shape in the middle of the cup. If that doesn't work either, I'll just have to accept what nature has given me, I guess, unless someone has some great tried and true recommendations to offer...

Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Men', 'Accessories', 'Hats & Caps', 'Sun Hats']]
Review Text: I love in South Florida and have tried numerous hats that claimed to have SPF protection combined with comfit of fit and wear.  Well this hat certainly has the required attributes.  I walk every morning and this is the first hat that I didn't have to hold when a breeze blew thru (albeit a seldom occurrence in my climate). It may not make a fashion statement (although no one will call you a "dork") but it certainly is functional and comfortable.

Review Text: I love these heels, they are absolutely adorable!  They seem very well made and I think they'll last a good long while.  The material is nice and soft, too. I followed the advice of the reviewer's and got a 1/2 size bigger (not that I had a choice, I got the smallest size available in this shoe).  I usually wear between a 5 and a 5.5 and I ordered a 6.  I know some people have said the size runs small but these were really big on me and seemed to be a standard US 6.  I had to pad them in the toe and underneath the ball of the foot but that's okay.  The shoes look great and they've very comfortable to walk in (if you're used to heels).  I could wear these all day and not feel it.  I would highly recommend these shoes.

Review Text: Summary: I will be buying several more of these jogging bras for backup. Great product, high quality!As a girl with an odd bra size (36A), it's hard to find a good bra that either is snug enough to hold my chest but isn't so tight to dig into my ribs. I can't think of how many bras (normal and exercise) that's I've bought and thrown out over the years. Even harder to factor in a preferred zip up front.This Yvette bra is soft, comfortable, yet breathable. At first I was worried that while running at 7+ MPH that my chest would be all over the place, yet everything stayed perfectly in place. Not too tight, not too loose. My skin could breath and sweat but straps stayed out and didn't shift even after an hour of hard running. This is an affordable yet high quality product for yoga, Pilates, aerobics, and cycling. Highly recommend!

Review Text: This jacket is wonderful in every way except for the way it's sewn together. The material is thick and soft, and the Sherpa lining is adequate and keeps you warm. Unfortunately, I wore the jacket a few times before I noticed that the seam on the inner side of the sleeve was not sewn correctly, exposing the inner lining. I was able to double over the fabric a little and sew the seam again, but it shouldn't have been necessary. Also, the extra thread around the area at the base of the zipper was not trimmed, so there are several hanging threads, making that area of the jacket appear unfinished. Overall, I love the jacket, but I cannot give it a higher rating due to the poor construction.

Review Text: This is a very pretty, all-cotton dress.  I chose the black version, so that I wouldn't have to wear a bra with it.  I'm 5'1" and 36" around at both the bust and hips. The dress fits me well, and the skirt length comes about mid-calf.  I think it's a pretty and flattering look. I haven't washed it yet, and I believe if it shrank it would still be flattering.  Yet I plan to air dry it after washing, because I like it's current length.  This is a dress that both shorter and taller women can wear.  You don't need a perfect tummy for this, because it is somewhat high waisted.  I intended to use this as something to throw on when I finished showering in the locker room after swimming.  I can still use it for that, but it is nice enough to wear out in the evening, especially with appropriate footwear.  So in all, it's a great multi-purpose dress for a great price.

Review Text: This suit fits exactly as the sizing chart describes. The only odd thing is stitching on the front that is only ornamental to suggest that there is an opening for us to use on visits to a restroom.  Well there is no opening there.  Think they could left that little detail out but it does not harm the suit and a front opening in a swim suit to me is more of a negative than positive.  It dried pretty quickly and the material is very soft.I see no signs that it will wear out quickly and it seems sturdy enough that it should last as long as any other suit I ever bought. I have pretty large thighs and the suit was not tight at all and did not restrict my legs movements at all.

Review Text: When I opened the box, I was disappointed as the shoes are gray, but I needed new shoes so I wore them...these are quite possibly the most comfortable shoes I have EVER put on my feet! They truly have relieved much of my lower body joint pain and make walking a pleasure. I don't ever want to take them off! If they were available in another color in my size, I would order another pair-they are THAT comfortable!I have lupus and am in pain management, I was told to wear Reebok or New Balance-but the New Balance just don't fit properly and aren't quite as stylish...being in my mid-30's, I am not ready to completely give up style for function. I have always had good luck with Reeboks, but these shoes are amazing! They look great and feel wonderful!They fit true to size(I wear 9, 9.5, or 10...these fit like a glove at 9.5-exactly my true size)

Review Text: We just got this so I haven't had a chance to use it yet....but wanted to comment on the look and fit.I originally got the Light Blue Hawaiian.  I thought it was cute, but my husband immediately said that it was too girly.  I can see what he means....the pattern is hard to mistake for just being "flowery".  I'm already putting his 20 month old son in speedos, and so I think the combo of that, the colors and pattern was a tad to much for him (and he isn't a machismo either...he wears skinny jeans and tight t shirts for example).  Needless to say, we switched it out for the darker blue one (thanks Amazon). Soo there's that.The fit seems right.  For my 20 month old who is about 22 lbs, I got the 24 month size.  I think the legs are right enough, although we shall see when a #2 happens (I will update).  My son is quite skinny though, so I would advise most who have this age to go with the 24 months because I think it will be tight but not too right (you know your kid though, and if he is 98% for weight, then size the kid up).We used an iplay diaper last year (white with buttons on the side), and it was great - but we never experienced a poo, so I don't know if it would have held (but I think it would have bc the legs were tight and every reviewer said it would).

Summary: If shoe was sized correctly, it would be 5 stars
Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Shoes & Accessories: International Shipping Available'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'N', 'New Balance'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Shoes', 'Athletic', 'Fitness & Cross-Training']]
Review Text: I read the other reviews regarding how New Balanced has severely reduced the sizing of their women's shoes, so I ordered a full size larger than I normally wear (including existing New Balance shoes).  The shoes that were shipped were marked 9AA.  The width was fine but the length was significantly too short.  I found another pair of New Balance shoes that has a similar tread pattern and compared the two.  When held together, the new shoe was 3/4" to 1" shorter than its counterpart.  This is either a change in manufacturing or an inattention to detail.  From what the other reviews have said, it would appear to be less of a variance in each shoe than an overall reduction of sizing.  Be careful what you order from New Balance.  I love their shoes but may not be able to order them on-line anymore.  Thank goodness for Amazon that allowed me to return the shoes the next day, with a full refund.

Summary: Pales in comparison to the Marcie
Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Clothing', 'Lingerie, Sleep & Lounge', 'Intimates', 'Bras', 'Everyday Bras'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Petite', 'Intimates', 'Bras', 'Everyday Bras']]
Review Text: This bra looks like it has very similar construction to Panache Marcie, but it is very different on.  The bras based on the Marcie styling have the impressive effect of making even really quite large busts seem to float.  This one compresses like a sports bra (in my opinion).  The Cleo sub-brand is often said to run small in the band, big in the cup, I haven't found this to be true (especially with this particular bra).  I bought this bra in my regular band and cup size and while the band is fine, I can't tell whether perhaps an H cup would have been a better bet, or if it's meant to be a minimizer.  As it is, it could function as a sports bra -- it keeps everything strapped down nicely.It does have great straps.  I've had issues with the straps rolling on some Panache bras (particularly Andorra), these are very stable.It's a comfortable bra and will keep you from bouncing, but you wouldn't want to show it to anyone.

Review Text: Champion Compression Under ShirtThere's not as much compression as I would like. Review Text: These shoes are plenty wide, but the toe design is all wrong! Since it kind of comes to a point near your big toe, they end up kind of "crunching" your toes together. Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Men', 'Clothing', 'Socks', 'Dress & Trouser Socks'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Men', 'Big & Tall']]
Review Text: My old socks had either worn out after years of use or slowly got nabbed by the Gripes in the laundry, so I ordered a set of Gold Toe knowing that those were supposed to be the name-brand.Straight out of the package, they look and feel very nice (they are a perfect thickness), and as you start to put them on, you think everything's going to be great, and that's where it ends.  Unfortunately, once I got the socks all the way on, I could feel a very distinct seam in the toe that was driving me nuts.  I tried adjusting the socks several times and swapping them for the other foot, but the seam was still very noticeable.On top of that, since they are polyester, they do tend to slip down my leg a little more than my old cotton socks.  By the end of the work day, they were slightly sweaty from being less breathable than cotton, though not terrible.I will wear these until they wear out or I get sick of them, because they're not terrible, but I would not buy these again.There is a similar style brand I used to buy that has a gold stripe on the toe instead of the gold block, but I can't remember the name and haven't been able to find them online at the moment.  I bought them at a military exchange store, and they were very comfortable and lasted me for years, but it's driving me crazy that I can't find them again.

Review Text: Great vest..nice large pockets (including 3 inside pockets), plus great ventilation system (mesh rear is covered by the cloth but has pleats allowing the air to come in easily. Has pen holders, if you carry pen and paper. True to size..I wanted one large enough to go over my jacket if necessary and it fit just fine, large armholes. Some of the velcro closures are a bit hard to tug open at first, so you need to loosen those up BEFORE you start wearing the vest. Material is lightweight but seems sturdy enough.

Review Text: well, this is my first lycra balaclava.  Polar fleece was getting too warm for Texas Spring.....but I had no idea they made these light weight ones with a thick seam running down the FRONT that by the end of the ride into a headwind practically slices your lips and nose in half.  Either make them seamless or do a better job of smoothing out the ridges in the seam.  Maybe guys are all tough and burly and don't notice, but I am a woman and not only is it very irritating, I had to run around with a big red stripe on my face for an hr after reaching my destination.  So, hunt for one of these face masks that is seamless. Other than that it is an awesome way to keep the wind off your face and neck, to keep your hair in place and to keep your helmet snug.

Review Text: I have a very hard time finding bras that fit. In this bra I'm a 34F (it runs a cup size large so order a cup size down), and it's very hard to find supportive bras that are durable, comfortable, and that hold the ladies up without looking ridiculous. This bra holds my breasts up where they belong, looks seamless under any shirt, and fits perfectly around my rib cage and under my arms. My husband commented that I've never looked better wearing a bra, which I think is a testament in itself. My ONLY complaint is that the material used for the straps makes them loosen easier than other bras I've owned, but it's as simple as tightening the straps every few days before I put on the bra. I'd recommend this to any ladies wanting a supportive bra that holds up :-)

Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Maternity', 'Intimates', 'Nursing & Maternity Bras'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Petite']]
Review Text: I was skeptical about ordering this since I had never heard of the company, but since there are very few options out there in nursing bras in my size, I decided to give it a try.  As soon as I put this bra on, I knew it wasn't going back!  I didn't have one nursing bra that truly fit, and now that I do, it's hard to put any of the others on anymore.  I ended up going to the Hotmilk website and ordering 2 more since this is the only style that Amazon carries (wish they carried more!).  The bra is really well made, very comfortable, and most importantly, supportive without underwire!  I would not have thought it was possible for a FF-cup bra to be so supportive without underwire.  It's amazing.  My one small issue with the bra is that the cup fabric is a bit more revealing than I would like it to be (nursing pads may show when you're wearing them).  However, I still give this five stars because all of the good things about it more than outweigh that small issue.

Review Text: I purchased this robe based on the brand and figured that since it was from Dearfoams, it must be pretty good. Boy, was I off base on that! It's been a few months and it already has a tear near the right pocket. Mind you, I only wear this robe after shower/bath time, so it doesn't get what I'd call "normal" wear. As far as it being too small, I'm not sure what other reviewers mean, because I bought a large (just for extra room) and it fits like a large! I'm 5'9, 147 pounds, and the large was plenty big. If you want something made from lycra or the sorts, pass on this one; or if you want 100 percent cotton, don't buy this one. All in all, I got what I paid for. Next time I'll spring for a better robe not one so cheap!

Review Text: I ordered the 32DD but I'm debating on returning it to try a 32D or just returning and trying something else.  I bought it for running, and I still had a little bit of bounce.  Plus the metal strap adjusters were hitting against my shoulder blades and I am afraid that on a long run I might end up with a bruise or chafing.Yes, it has a pretty high rise in the front, a little higher than I would prefer.  I'm not trying to show anything, but I can't stand coverage in that area b/c I tend to sweat a lot right there and I think I'd get too hot too quickly.  Also, the double layering of the cup area (in particular the fabric used) makes me think that it might be pretty hot for running on a humid southern day.I liked the separation and definition, however.  Definitely not a typical uni-boob sports bra.

Summary: I won't go back to normal soled running shoes
Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Shoes & Accessories: International Shipping Available'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'N', 'New Balance'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Shoes', 'Athletic', 'Running']]
Review Text: I've had these for 6 months and I love these shoes.  I can't go back to normal running shoes.  These shoes have enabled me to adapt a mid-strike running style which has allowed me to lean more over my toes (less upright) and make my running overall more efficient and less taxing.  I have no pain from sore muscles running anymore.  In fact, I use running to get over my sore calves or quads from strength training when I get too ambitious.I wear these mostly without socks, but it doesn't bother me to wear them with thin socks when it's cold outside.  And, because there's no toe thing to contend with, that is an option - unlike other minimalist shoes.I have talked my husband into getting the men's version of these shoes to help with his aching/weak calves and knee pain.  I will by another pair of these whenever my shoes wear out.  They show no signs of wear on the outside - so that may be awhile.

Review Text: I was so excited to find wide-width open-toe pumps, since I was looking for basic comfortable black sandal/open-toed pumps to wear to work every day. However, these were quite disappointing.Firstly, the sides of the shoes don't come up high enough, even on the wide-width shoe. My feet are only slightly wide and I can usually get away with medium-width shoes, but these made my feet look monstrous because they sides were folding down under my feet.Second, the platforms are shaped in a weird angle as if they were meant for a higher heel, so they're not flush to the floor unless I'm leaning forward. They take a while to get used to.The heel is smaller and comfortable, but I have 4-5 inch heels that fit and feel more comfortable than these. They are definitely going back.

Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Watches', 'Wrist Watches']]
Review Text: I was very hesitant to order this watch after reading a lot of the reviews- many were bad. This seems to be a hit-or-miss product. Mine arrived today, it had all of the rhinestones in place, no marks on it and appears to be in perfect condition. The watch does look exactly like the picture, or at least mine does. I have read reviews others have written saying it didn't look like the picture or that it looks like something from the dollar store- that I don't agree with. The band is too big for my wrist (I'd say I have normal size wrists) so I will probably have one link removed and then it should fit perfectly. The only part about this watch that feels cheap to me is the band itself. It is heavier than plastic would be but the way it feels when you're holding it- you can feel that it's cheaply made. Wearing it on my wrist, however, I think it looks nice and I think people would think it was a $200 watch. I am going to put clear nailpolish over the rhinestones and on the inside of the band as I have read other reviews saying the band may turn your skin green and some have complained that rhinestones fell out shortly after they bought it.All in all, decent watch- especially for the $8 I paid for it. Looks MUCH more expensive than $8, that is undeniable. I am looking forward to rocking this watch and shocking people when I tell them how inexpensive it was.

Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Petite', 'Active', 'Athletic Socks']]
Review Text: I have suffered years with debilitating cramps in my toes and feet for decades. If my feet get the least bit cold, the cramping starts. I ordered a pair of electric booties and a pair of these. The electric booties were uncomfortable and got too hot very quickly. Needless to say, that product was returned. However these little beauties do exactly what I thought the electric booties would do. They keep my toes toasty warm without making them sweaty and too hot. The insides are super soft and cushy. I put these on the minute I get home from work, and even wear them to bed. I've had these for over a week, and I've not had a single foot cramp! I normally experience foot cramps daily, so to be cramp-free for over a week is a godsend. I just ordered a pair of the slipper sock version too. I cannot recommend these socks highly enough!

Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Gemstones'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Jewelry', 'Fine', 'Earrings', 'Stud'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Novelty, Costumes & More', 'Novelty']]
Review Text: Love the stones on these but as some have stated the post is set at the top of the stone instead of in the middle. This doesn't matter to me, I have a couple of these pairs and they wear normally just sit a bit lower than normal. However, after having been wearing earrings for over 20 years I can honestly say that I have never had a pair that the post will bend as easily as these. I bent one just trying to put the back on them in my ear, it was easy to bend back if done carefully. They hold up well to daily wear with only minor bending from sleeping etc in them. Overall, I would still buy them again and would not be ashamed to give them as a gift.

Summary: Casio Men's Atomic Solar G Shock GWM850-1CR; Solid Watch
Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'New Arrivals'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Men', 'Watches', 'Wrist Watches']]
Review Text: I just received this watch and have been using it daily. The packaging was excellent, the shipping time was longer than expected due to the inclement weather back East.My present Casio, the JC-30 has been in service for several years and is finally showing wear and tear. I hope this new Casio watch lasts as many years as the JC-30.The GWM850-1CR is a sleeker Casio G Shock model than many of the other Casio G Shocks on the market today. It is not as extreme in the height, width and overall size of the watch. It has a sleek and solid appearence and will not stand out on the wrist.The bezel is made of a clean, smooth appearing stainless steel and will also provide damage protection from everyday use.The face of the watch is a light shade of gray, with black colored data such as the day, date and time. The face of the watch has a clean and uncluttered appearance with the top window displaying the day and the date. The day and the date is hard to read, the letters and digits are very small. Unless you have excellent eye sight or glasses, this could be a slight problem. This is the only complaint I have about this watch. The top window also displays world time when this feature is activated.The bottom window displays the horizional battery charge, the solar battery strength, snooze, alarm, sig alerts, solar cell and the time. The numbers are easy to read and the bottom window is well designed.Directly above the watch data is a textured dark gray colored front with two windows that is both functional and gives the watch a better appearance and quality than you would expect from a watch at this price point.The four buttons A,B,C,D are well placed and have a slight elevated protective perimeter from the body of the watch so the buttons can not be pressed inadvertently. It takes a bit of pressure to activate the button. Button L, located at the botton center of the watch will provide back light to the watch in low light conditions. The back light is adequate, but not really bright.The wrist band is made of a textured resin material with duel clasps. The wrist band appears to be molded or structured around the watch and it gives a good looking appearance. I'm hoping that the wrist band is made of a strong and long lasting resin. It is not known how difficult it will be to replace the wrist band when it wears out.This watch has many features, such as atomic time keeping, solar power, standard or military time format,(12/24) world time, stop watch, count down timer, rally feature, multiple alarms, snooze, hour beeper and auto (EL) back light. The audible alerts are not loud, rather the sound is soft and muted. The watch also has a automatic power saver shutdown in darkness. This feature saves power during non-operation.The watch also comes with an impressive 119 page manual that provides detailed information about the watch features, functions and how to operate the watch.Unless you are a rocket scientist or a brain surgeon, it will take a little time and a little effort to understand the methods and procedures to operate all the features:)Pros: Solar powered, atomic timekeeping, sleek smooth appearing stainless steel bezel and packed with many features. Great watch at price point and well worth the price.Cons: The top window that displays the font/lettering/numbers for the day and date are small to read.Conclusion: All in all, this is a well designed watch with a standard size and sleeker design. Also, it is a great watch for the price point.Update: As of March, 2014, I have owned this watch for over four years and it has performed perfectly.I wear it everyday and the watch takes significant use and impacts in the work environment. Due to the great construction materials, the watch and the resin wrist band have held up extremely well. There have been no defects in construction materials and the performance of the watch.I'm very pleased with the quality and features of this watch.Jon Green

Review Text: I recently came across these very same hats at a local mall this past Christmas.  As an avid walker and hiker, even in the dead of winter I am always looking for something a little warmer and more comfortable with the least amount of effort to put on, or carry along.  For years there was the traditional knit hat, or toque that was on my list as standard equipment both for walking and hiking.  That is until I tried one of these on at the mall this past holiday season and decided that they have easily incorporated into the design of these the 3 essentials necessary for keeping warm and comfy while braving the winters savage elements.  A knit toque for the head, an extended ear flap to take care of the ears, and a visor for the very obvious reasons as to why we very often need one.  Quite simply put, I found these hats to be far more warm and comfy than the traditional toque for surviving the long winter here in New England.  Most of all, I wish that I had located the hats here before buying a couple at the local mall.  They are not only cheaper here than what I paid, but as of the time of this writing, ship for free through Amazon.  If you spend a lot of time outside in winter and desire the ultimate in head gear as far as warmth and convenience in my opinion, invest in two or more of these and be done for life.  They are warm, comfy, and at the price they are asking for them with free shipping, its like you are buying them tax free and at cost from your local store, and having them delivered to your house for free... Recommended.

Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Shoes & Accessories: International Shipping Available'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'N', 'Nine West'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Boot Shop'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Shoes', 'Boots']]
Review Text: LONG review, but I am providing info I always wish I had before a purchase...most important, this boot is GORGEOUS.  I was looking at the brown color, but it sold out in my size.  I saw the "grey" color, and since I only choose to purchase LEATHER boots, I ordered them in "grey leather."  to my happy surprise they are NOT grey- the are a neutral taupe, almost a medium beige color- I love them, the color is so easy to match with black, but even brown.the small zipper on the ankle is just right for getting your foot in, and is fairly unnoticeable. the braid trim along the entire shaft is what makes these boots stunning- makes me want to wear them with a skirt!some reviewers have complained about the mock distressing- I do agree, it's unnecessary and a bit of a glitch- it appears to be some type of wax applied to the spots- it is not distressed or dyed.  I used a wire brush to soften up the spots and it helped to resurface the original material, but not 100%.  it is fairly subtle, and I am sure if I don't like it in the future, I can take it to a shoe shop for a really inexpensive touch-up.My shoe size is normally anywhere from 8 - 9 depending on the type of shoe- with boots I usually order a 9 because I can wear a heavy sock. These boots are roomy in the toe box, and with a 9 I even had wiggle-room.

Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Shoes & Accessories: International Shipping Available'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'M', 'Michael Antonio'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Shoes', 'Boots']]
Review Text: These shoes were designed for foot torture. Generally, I am the woman who wears stilettos to check the mail, eat a hotdog, or run a marathon. My feet are designed for impossible footwear. However, I wore these shoes to a basketball game, and I knew I was in trouble when my feet began to throb and go numb just by wearing them while sitting in the car. By the time I'd walked through the parking lot to the arena, my feet were bloody stumps.Seriously, only after about an hour, blisters were forming on the balls of my feet and every single toe. Walking in these cheap foot-manglers became literally impossible. I ended up chucking them off, and walking through a filthy downtown city in my stocking feet like an idiot.At $25, it's still no deal to have only been able to wear these shoes once. In fact, it's the exact same thing as paying someone $25 to smash your toes with a hammer.For foot torture enthusiasts: They do run true to size, and arrive quickly.Sane people: Don't buy!

Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Shoes & Accessories: International Shipping Available'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Summer Event'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'R', 'Reef'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Street, Surf & Skate'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Shoes', 'Sandals']]
Review Text: When I first got these in the mail I thought they would not last a week; they are very light. However, they've been the most comfortable flip flops I've ever had! Their lightness makes them easy to walk in, and they contour my feet very well. Since I live in Tucson I've worn these almost every day for the past six months and they still look great.UPDATE: I've had these a year now, still wearing them almost every day, and they are STILL going strong! The treads have worn off the bottom so I no longer wear them when it's raining, but usually it's the straps that break on a flip flop. But the straps on these gems are still fully intact (besides a bit of fuzz on the fabric)!

Review Text: WOW!!!! This thing is gorgeous! It has a really beach-y, Hawaiian look which is perfect for the summer time. I found myself looking at my feet a lot just because I love how it looks! I Already got a lot of compliments on it and I've only had it for about a week. One thing is certain, this toe ring will stay on until summer is over and even then I'll probably be sporting it on my hand =)

Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Shoes & Accessories: International Shipping Available'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'T', 'Timberland'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Boot Shop', 'Women', 'Fashion', 'Shearling'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Boot Shop', 'Women', 'Outdoor & Work', 'Snow & Cold Weather'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Shoes', 'Boots']]
Review Text: I LOVE these boots.  I'm an 8-8.5 & because only the 8 was available in the Amazon Wharehouse Deals & it saved me about $50 I got the 8.  I could've use an 8.5 I suppose but it's not bad even with thin socks.  I'm 5'9" 135lbs, small but athletic frame & these boots zipped up easily over skinny & straight leg jeans.  As many reviewers said & IMO these are better than Uggs & at 39yrs old maybe a more serious option over the over-done college look of Uggs as well.  The toe box offers nice wiggle room & the only minor complaint I have is that with my high arches the top of my mid-foot gets a little sore after 5-6hrs of wearing so I may have them stretched a little to help that IF they don't stretch soon.  I took them out of the box & wore them all day...feet that are normally sensitive to cold felt nice & warm as did my legs.  Looking forward to many Chicago winter days in them.  Loved them so much I got them in black & dark brown via Amazon Wharehouse Deals. I've become a huge Timberland fan.

Review Text: I bought this to replace my leather wallet, which was falling apart.  I also wanted a fixed size, so my wallet doesn't end up being the catch-all for everything.  I've used it about two weeks now, and it seems to work quite well.  I like the "rolodex" expanding folder-style presentation when you open it, which makes it easy to find what I'm looking for - no more digging endlessly for my Costco or ACE hardware cards!It holds a fair amount of cards, but once you go over a certain limit, it won't close, and the span from working normally to not working is 1 or two cards, it seems.  I have my Driver's License, Debit/Credit card, Starbucks Gold Card, ACE Hardware, Costco, 5 business cards, a wallet photo, AAA card, health insurance card, Rifle Club card, and my NRA card... More than enough for me!  I have space for maybe 2 more cards before it won't close.  Money takes up a lot of space, but I don't typically carry cash, but a couple of Twenties probably would fit OK.Over all, it seems pretty durable, stays closed, and works like I wanted it to.  My only real negative is that the surface is smoother than I'd like, and it feels slippery in my pocket.  I'd prefer a texture or rubberized surface in order for me to feel better about it.  It hasn't been an issue, but its more of a confidence thing.  I'd recommend this thing, and have shown it to others.

I am returning it and getting him a large like I would have ordered him in the first place.This shirt is 100% cotton, so I will expect some shrinking after washing it the first time as I should because it is 100% cotton.  (Hence ordering him a Large)  The shirt was thin, but not flimsy, just a light shirt, as one will need for about half the Christmases we have in the south. He did too and was disappointed that it was too large, so we coudn't wash it for him to wear later that evening.I kinda hate it that I couldn't exchange it, but I am returning it and ordering another in the correct size.

Review Text: Love the watch, the strap is identical to the other Citizen chronograph canvas strap model. For the me the strap is too short on both models for my wrist. Review Text: I do a lot of high impact classes and these are doing a great job at keeping my feet comfortable.  I usually have problems with not enough cushioning in the ball of the foot area. In the future I may have to get new insoles, but like I said, so far so good.  This model does run a half size larger is my feeling.  One thing I don't really care for is the white on the sides is more like a shiny vinyl rather than leather or a cloth product.  (That's why I gave it 4 stars instead of 5.) Some reviews say it's tough to get foot in the heel area where there is a soft backing, but I think it's fine.  Update:  It's been 6 months of 5 times a week working out and did change the insoles, but that's pretty impressive.  I really like these shoes.

Categories: [['Sports & Outdoors', 'Exercise & Fitness', 'Yoga', 'Clothing', 'Women', 'Pants'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Clothing', 'Active', 'Active Pants']]
Review Text: I measure at just about 5' tall so finding pants (and all clothing) that fit is difficult. These pants are true to size, they look exactly as pictured, the description is accurate from the material (the style, fit, and appearance) and as for the length, they're just a tad too long.  Just a tad. They're comfortable, compared to other "athletic" pants, they offer gentle compression, and the slight flair to the leg adds balance.  I love the waistband, it's comfortable, stylish, enhances the fit, and does not roll down! They're beautiful.  Look good, feel great. High quality (unlike some "yoga pants" that turn out to be cheaply made). I go through athletic pants rapidly because they stretch out in certain areas, sag, develop puffy spots, like the knees, because they're not made well and the fabric wears thin and ends up looking like you've got stains. These pants are cut to both enhance the shape of the female frame, (the seams are very well placed and do not chafe or bulge), and allow just the right amount of stretch, and support, to hold up during long activities requiring a lot of leg movement. (No sagging, puffy draping, or random "loose sections" that are quickly worn thin that I've seen in lesser quality made athletic apparel).  No complaints.

Summary: My go to bag, I'm buying a second color.
Categories: [['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Handbags & Wallets', 'Top-Handle Bags'], ['Clothing, Shoes & Jewelry', 'Women', 'Handbags & Wallets', 'Shoulder Bags']]
Review Text: I have a closet full of other bags, in every style out there, but I always seem to go back to this one. I have owned it in black for over a year, and am buying the Khaki for spring/summer. It simply for me is the most functional everyday work/commuter bag I have found. I'm an urban commuter, walk to the train and around the city everyday. The drop is perfect (no struggling to get it on my shoulder over a winter coat, or having to hang on tight to stop it from sliding down my arm, no strangling myself with a clunky cross body strap with a heavy bag flopping around on my hip), it sits easily on my shoulder,comfortably under my arm, is easy to get on and off. The three big outer pockets are perfect to slip in an umbrella (always need to have one with me),sunglasses,water bottle,newspaper, gloves,Ipod, pair of flats or anything else I might need . The bag has a nice wide zippered opening, no struggling to get into the bag to grab my wallet,then digging into the abyss groping for it.The slide and zipper pockets inside, keep my keys, phone, wallet etc. securely in the same spot everday where I can find them, no fumbling with sticky zippers on oddly placed pockets to grab my phone or find my makeup bag. Roomy enough to get everything else I need in it without feeling like a suitcase.(My Kindle and Tablet PC fit easily, my 14" laptop is a tight fit-I rarely carry it.).Love the feet on the bottom, the bag stands and keeps its shape when I put it down. The outside double zipper pocket will hold any files I need with me, or unzipped, will slide over my carryon handle when traveling. I am really hard on my bags, I also walk in rain and snow and it has held up well, including the rolled handles (haven't had the same trouble as some other reviewers have had with the straps.) I too wish Baggallini would update it's color choices (especially the lining colors. I'm not sure how I'm going to like the "Caspian Blue" lining that comes in the Khaki-a really odd choice in my opinion),but I'm willing to deal with it because this bag just works for me. It's not the most fashionable bag I own,but it is classic and professional enough for me to feel comfortable carrying into a business meeting.

Review Text: I've tried both sizes 6 and 6.5. Size 6 is hard to get on, then feels tight. Size 6.5 is easy to get on, but feels tight width-wise at the heel, while also feeling loose overall as I walk around! My heel kept slipping up as I take each step. So it was obviously loose overall but still narrow for me.It was a really weird fit, I don't know how else to say it. It's too bad because these are beautiful, well-made boots and I would have loved to find the right size.I think that overall, I've found that the Frye boots that I've tried on here and there over the years, are not good for small feet that are also on the wide-side of average. The small sizes seem to accommodate only narrow feet.

Review Text: Kipling purses, totes and small duffle bags, are all of excellent quality and last forever.  They are well made and have great zippers.This Europa is no exception.  I bought it for traveling and it holds what I need for a days activities, and my point and shoot camera fits into the front outside pocket perfectly.The only thing that I didn't like about it, is the interior section which they separated with a thin lining material, making it two separate sections.  I prefer a single interior - wide open.So, and I am not recommending this to everyone, my husband carefully cut away that piece of material which is nylon, and even more carefully burned the cut edges with a match to seal them so they wouldn't unravel.  Again, do this at your own discretion and do it slowly and carefully.
